1
00:00:00,805 --> 00:00:02,745
(It's a lovely day in June,)

2
00:00:02,745 --> 00:00:05,345
(perfect to go on a trip.)

3
00:00:05,845 --> 00:00:09,755
(An emerald green lake...)

4
00:00:09,755 --> 00:00:12,725
(and a sea of purple flowers blanket the East Sea.)

5
00:00:13,425 --> 00:00:16,155
(Where are we going today that's so exciting?)

6
00:00:16,155 --> 00:00:17,155
You're here early.

7
00:00:17,155 --> 00:00:18,155
- Yes.
- Good.

8
00:00:18,155 --> 00:00:19,425
- Hello.
- Hi.

9
00:00:19,425 --> 00:00:20,765
You lost weight, Joon.

10
00:00:20,765 --> 00:00:22,095
- Really?
- Are you a balloon?

11
00:00:22,295 --> 00:00:24,035
Yes. You're no longer so bulky.

12
00:00:24,035 --> 00:00:25,595
- Your chest...
- It wasn't like that.

13
00:00:25,595 --> 00:00:26,935
You exercised your whole life,

14
00:00:26,935 --> 00:00:28,835
and you look like this after just a few days?

15
00:00:29,205 --> 00:00:31,305
You look so different after just two weeks.

16
00:00:31,305 --> 00:00:32,575
You lost that in two weeks?

17
00:00:32,575 --> 00:00:34,145
Your pecs used to stick out.

18
00:00:34,145 --> 00:00:35,345
- They're gone.
- Actually?

19
00:00:35,345 --> 00:00:36,975
But if I exercise for two weeks,

20
00:00:37,075 --> 00:00:38,345
- for our next shoot, - Oh, really?

21
00:00:38,345 --> 00:00:39,985
- I can bulk up.
- You can?

22
00:00:39,985 --> 00:00:41,485
Change your name to "Two Weeks."

23
00:00:42,215 --> 00:00:43,255
You have a new name?

24
00:00:43,255 --> 00:00:44,685
- Two Weeks.
- It has a nice ring to it.

25
00:00:44,685 --> 00:00:46,255
- A lot happens in two weeks.
- Yes.

26
00:00:46,325 --> 00:00:48,185
- Two weeks pass in no time.
- Yes.

27
00:00:48,885 --> 00:00:51,025
- It's Friday already.
- I can't believe it.

28
00:00:51,195 --> 00:00:53,465
We trod on as time just flew by.

29
00:00:53,465 --> 00:00:54,465
Yes.

30
00:00:54,465 --> 00:00:56,135
It's lovely. It's a great day.

31
00:00:56,135 --> 00:00:57,335
(A sea of early-summer purple)

32
00:00:57,335 --> 00:00:58,365
Isn't this lavender?

33
00:00:58,365 --> 00:00:59,405
- What's this?
- Lavender?

34
00:00:59,405 --> 00:01:00,665
- How beautiful.
- "Lazenca, Save Us."

35
00:01:00,665 --> 00:01:01,905
It looks insane.

36
00:01:01,905 --> 00:01:03,035
(In awe)

37
00:01:04,105 --> 00:01:05,905
(It's a captivating sight.)

38
00:01:05,905 --> 00:01:08,105
It's beautiful here. I want a photo.

39
00:01:08,905 --> 00:01:10,615
- It smells.
- You smell lavender?

40
00:01:10,615 --> 00:01:11,945
- Yes.
- It's nice.

41
00:01:11,945 --> 00:01:13,945
(Each step brings them closer to the gentle aroma.)

42
00:01:14,445 --> 00:01:16,185
The Republic of Korea!

43
00:01:17,785 --> 00:01:19,285
What about today's soccer match?

44
00:01:19,455 --> 00:01:21,185
- We should watch.
- What's the plan?

45
00:01:21,325 --> 00:01:23,295
It's not far off. It's two hours away.

46
00:01:23,295 --> 00:01:25,725
- It attacks at 10am, right?
- Yes.

47
00:01:25,725 --> 00:01:27,165
There's no attack. It's just a match.

48
00:01:28,095 --> 00:01:29,695
- You...
- You're like Joon.

49
00:01:29,695 --> 00:01:31,465
You're becoming too much like him.

50
00:01:31,465 --> 00:01:32,935
Don't stick together.

51
00:01:33,035 --> 00:01:34,265
- It's a 10am match.
- Hey.

52
00:01:34,265 --> 00:01:36,035
There's some good news. Yong Jin joined too,

53
00:01:36,035 --> 00:01:38,375
but Ki Taek won over the public.

54
00:01:38,835 --> 00:01:40,505
- Yes.
- These days...

55
00:01:40,505 --> 00:01:42,445
- Thank you.
- They say you're handsome.

56
00:01:42,445 --> 00:01:43,645
- Everyone loves him.
- Yes.

57
00:01:43,645 --> 00:01:45,745
- The moms love him.
- For real?

58
00:01:45,745 --> 00:01:47,485
It's like he's their first love from when they were 20.

59
00:01:47,485 --> 00:01:48,685
- Really?
- Really.

60
00:01:48,685 --> 00:01:50,185
They're enamored.

61
00:01:50,185 --> 00:01:52,185
- Don't moms love you?
- Their first love.

62
00:01:52,185 --> 00:01:53,425
They do like me a lot.

63
00:01:53,425 --> 00:01:54,585
- Right?
- Yes.

64
00:01:54,585 --> 00:01:56,195
I went to a pharmacy recently.

65
00:01:56,395 --> 00:01:57,855
- You didn't have to pay?
- No.

66
00:01:57,855 --> 00:01:59,695
- Free medication?
- They worried about me.

67
00:01:59,695 --> 00:02:00,765
"Don't fall ill."

68
00:02:00,765 --> 00:02:02,625
"You need to shoot 2 Days 1 Night."

69
00:02:02,625 --> 00:02:03,635
(How touching.)

70
00:02:03,635 --> 00:02:05,495
- They were concerned.
- There's a huge fuss.

71
00:02:05,495 --> 00:02:07,535
Yes. They like me a lot.

72
00:02:07,705 --> 00:02:08,805
After my first appearance,

73
00:02:08,805 --> 00:02:10,435
after I slept outside,

74
00:02:10,435 --> 00:02:12,335
I went to my regular Chinese medicine clinic.

75
00:02:12,535 --> 00:02:13,775
As soon as I walked in,

76
00:02:13,775 --> 00:02:15,045
- the staff said...
- Said what?

77
00:02:15,045 --> 00:02:16,745
"I knew you'd be here!"

78
00:02:16,745 --> 00:02:17,745
Honestly.

79
00:02:17,745 --> 00:02:19,045
I got acupuncture done right away.

80
00:02:19,045 --> 00:02:20,745
- What?
- 2 Days 1 Night does that.

81
00:02:20,745 --> 00:02:22,085
"I knew you'd be here!"

82
00:02:22,085 --> 00:02:23,755
"He'll be here tomorrow."

83
00:02:23,755 --> 00:02:24,985
"I knew you'd be here."

84
00:02:24,985 --> 00:02:26,355
- It was tough.
- Oh, my gosh.

85
00:02:26,655 --> 00:02:28,055
(Let's start in a lavender sea.)

86
00:02:28,055 --> 00:02:29,085
Everyone.

87
00:02:29,495 --> 00:02:32,155
- It's time to start the trip.
- Okay.

88
00:02:32,155 --> 00:02:33,765
- We'll give you something.
- What?

89
00:02:35,365 --> 00:02:36,365
(What is that?)

90
00:02:36,365 --> 00:02:38,235
Are we going somewhere separately?

91
00:02:38,335 --> 00:02:39,465
Gangwon Province?

92
00:02:39,465 --> 00:02:40,835
- The east coast?
- It's a coastal thing.

93
00:02:40,835 --> 00:02:43,435
What's this? Why is there a long thing?

94
00:02:43,705 --> 00:02:45,575
Does the map remind you of something?

95
00:02:45,975 --> 00:02:48,105
Samcheok is where I did my army service.

96
00:02:48,105 --> 00:02:49,445
- Really?
- Samcheok.

97
00:02:49,445 --> 00:02:50,515
With the maritime police.

98
00:02:50,515 --> 00:02:51,515
Right now...

99
00:02:51,515 --> 00:02:53,585
- My maternal grandma.
- Your mom's mom?

100
00:02:53,585 --> 00:02:54,845
- Uljin?
- You had lots of snow crabs?

101
00:02:54,845 --> 00:02:56,115
Yes, of course. Uljin.

102
00:02:56,115 --> 00:02:58,615
- Why is there a line?
- Down to Busan.

103
00:02:58,915 --> 00:03:00,955
- What is this?
- Up to Goseong?

104
00:03:00,955 --> 00:03:02,795
- Isn't it a coastal road?
- A coastal road.

105
00:03:02,795 --> 00:03:03,825
You're right.

106
00:03:03,825 --> 00:03:07,595
This map shows Route Seven.

107
00:03:07,595 --> 00:03:09,395
- This is the 7th?
- Route 7.

108
00:03:09,595 --> 00:03:11,795
Its northernmost point is Goseong,

109
00:03:11,795 --> 00:03:14,065
and it goes all the way to Busan.

110
00:03:14,165 --> 00:03:17,035
It's called the Spine of Korea.

111
00:03:17,275 --> 00:03:19,405
- The spine.
- The tiger's spine.

112
00:03:19,405 --> 00:03:20,945
- The tiger's spine.
- Yes.

113
00:03:21,205 --> 00:03:22,815
For 2 days and 1 night,

114
00:03:22,815 --> 00:03:25,775
we'll follow Route Seven and enjoy the scenery.

115
00:03:25,775 --> 00:03:27,945
(The view of the East Sea along Route 7)

116
00:03:27,945 --> 00:03:29,755
We'll also taste some great food.

117
00:03:29,755 --> 00:03:31,615
(Enjoy good food)

118
00:03:31,615 --> 00:03:34,125
It's the Healing Along Route Seven trip.

119
00:03:34,485 --> 00:03:35,985
- Really?
- Good food?

120
00:03:36,085 --> 00:03:37,225
We travel south?

121
00:03:37,855 --> 00:03:40,495
We'll follow the coast down to Busan?

122
00:03:41,025 --> 00:03:42,765
- It took four hours to get here.
- Yes.

123
00:03:42,765 --> 00:03:43,835
Going further south...

124
00:03:44,065 --> 00:03:46,165
We'll drive enough to equal a world tour.

125
00:03:46,335 --> 00:03:48,105
We could've gone from here to here.

126
00:03:48,105 --> 00:03:49,435
We came here to go...

127
00:03:49,435 --> 00:03:51,405
- What logic is that?
- That's just...

128
00:03:51,405 --> 00:03:53,145
We must go all this way after we're done.

129
00:03:53,145 --> 00:03:55,045
We're circling the whole of Korea.

130
00:03:55,845 --> 00:03:58,075
Route 7 passes through 6 cities in Gangwon Province.

131
00:03:58,345 --> 00:04:00,685
Out of those six places,

132
00:04:00,685 --> 00:04:02,785
Jong Min chose where to film today's opening.

133
00:04:03,555 --> 00:04:04,815
- You?
- Why?

134
00:04:04,815 --> 00:04:06,255
- There was a meeting?
- Yes.

135
00:04:06,255 --> 00:04:07,255
When?

136
00:04:07,255 --> 00:04:08,255
(What is this about?)

137
00:04:08,255 --> 00:04:10,495
(Two days before filming)

138
00:04:10,495 --> 00:04:11,955
What's this?

139
00:04:11,955 --> 00:04:13,065
(The crew cornered Jong Min on "The Return of Superman.")

140
00:04:13,065 --> 00:04:14,525
- Take a seat.
- What's this?

141
00:04:15,165 --> 00:04:16,935
Why are you at my other workplace?

142
00:04:17,495 --> 00:04:18,795
What are you doing here?

143
00:04:19,335 --> 00:04:20,835
- You get the chance...
- Yes?

144
00:04:21,135 --> 00:04:24,405
to decide where the next trip starts.

145
00:04:24,405 --> 00:04:25,435
- Me?
- Yes.

146
00:04:26,805 --> 00:04:28,075
- I spin that?
- Yes.

147
00:04:28,075 --> 00:04:29,275
(He chooses 1 of the 6 Gangwon cities!)

148
00:04:29,275 --> 00:04:30,715
It goes down to Busan.

149
00:04:31,515 --> 00:04:33,015
- From Goseong.
- Yes.

150
00:04:33,115 --> 00:04:36,185
Our members' fate is in my hands!

151
00:04:36,955 --> 00:04:38,085
One, two,

152
00:04:38,685 --> 00:04:39,725
three!

153
00:04:39,725 --> 00:04:42,155
(2 Days 1 Night)

154
00:04:42,155 --> 00:04:44,995
(He decides the members' fate!)

155
00:04:44,995 --> 00:04:46,625
Sokcho...

156
00:04:46,625 --> 00:04:48,495
Yangyang, Sokcho, Goseong, Donghae,

157
00:04:48,495 --> 00:04:50,395
Gangneung, Yangyang, Donghae...

158
00:04:50,765 --> 00:04:51,795
Donghae!

159
00:04:52,295 --> 00:04:54,135
(2 Days 1 Night: Donghae)

160
00:04:54,135 --> 00:04:55,665
Donghae!

161
00:04:56,575 --> 00:04:57,805
Good job.

162
00:04:57,805 --> 00:04:59,235
- Well done.
- You chose well.

163
00:04:59,405 --> 00:05:00,705
(Relieved)

164
00:05:00,705 --> 00:05:03,845
If you chose Goseong, then...

165
00:05:03,845 --> 00:05:05,015
I'd have kept it a secret.

166
00:05:05,015 --> 00:05:06,015
(He'd have denied it.)

167
00:05:06,015 --> 00:05:07,185
- You'd keep quiet?
- Yes.

168
00:05:07,685 --> 00:05:10,655
We'll start the trip along Route Seven.

169
00:05:10,915 --> 00:05:13,955
Today's base camp is in Gyeongju,

170
00:05:14,285 --> 00:05:15,685
which is on Route Seven.

171
00:05:15,855 --> 00:05:17,125
- Gyeongju.
- Gyeongju?

172
00:05:17,255 --> 00:05:20,595
You have until 6pm today to follow Route 7,

173
00:05:20,595 --> 00:05:23,495
complete all the missions between Donghae of Gangwon Province...

174
00:05:23,495 --> 00:05:26,135
and Gyeongju of North Gyeongsang Province,

175
00:05:26,365 --> 00:05:28,005
and reach the base camp.

176
00:05:28,005 --> 00:05:29,335
It's a group thing.

177
00:05:29,335 --> 00:05:30,975
Yes. You're in this together.

178
00:05:31,175 --> 00:05:33,645
We traveled the route and calculated the travel time,

179
00:05:33,775 --> 00:05:35,645
as well as the time needed for each mission.

180
00:05:35,645 --> 00:05:37,975
- You'll have enough time.
- Okay.

181
00:05:38,115 --> 00:05:39,215
- Wait.
- It's fine.

182
00:05:39,215 --> 00:05:41,315
What's important is what happens if we fail.

183
00:05:41,315 --> 00:05:42,745
- Yes.
- Explain that, please.

184
00:05:43,455 --> 00:05:44,585
What if we fail?

185
00:05:45,055 --> 00:05:47,285
You must get out of the car wherever you are at 6pm.

186
00:05:48,085 --> 00:05:49,385
- And then...
- What then?

187
00:05:49,385 --> 00:05:51,395
- to the base camp...
- What?

188
00:05:51,395 --> 00:05:53,165
- We find our way?
- You must walk.

189
00:05:53,165 --> 00:05:54,325
- On foot?
- Yes.

190
00:05:55,565 --> 00:05:56,635
(We must arrive before 6pm.)

191
00:05:56,635 --> 00:05:58,165
- Well...
- Yes.

192
00:05:58,165 --> 00:05:59,665
(We must arrive before 6pm.)

193
00:05:59,735 --> 00:06:01,235
Let's get as close as we can.

194
00:06:01,235 --> 00:06:03,505
- We'll manage.
- About 10km...

195
00:06:03,505 --> 00:06:04,775
- Can you walk?
- That's fine, right?

196
00:06:04,775 --> 00:06:06,675
- That's doable.
- After my last shoot,

197
00:06:06,675 --> 00:06:07,945
I went jogging right away.

198
00:06:08,275 --> 00:06:10,975
- You went to the clinic.
- After my jog.

199
00:06:10,975 --> 00:06:12,775
I can walk up to 10km.

200
00:06:12,775 --> 00:06:13,815
- Yes.
- Yes.

201
00:06:13,815 --> 00:06:15,115
- He's fit.
- 10km is doable.

202
00:06:15,115 --> 00:06:16,215
- He's slim.
- I can do 10km.

203
00:06:16,215 --> 00:06:17,985
We all marched that far in the army.

204
00:06:18,785 --> 00:06:20,685
Se Yoon carried Ki Taek on his shoulders,

205
00:06:20,685 --> 00:06:22,325
- and that went viral.
- Yes.

206
00:06:22,325 --> 00:06:24,725
- This time Ki Taek can carry you.
- Perfect.

207
00:06:24,725 --> 00:06:25,925
- It'll look nice.
- 10km?

208
00:06:25,925 --> 00:06:26,925
Ten kilometers?

209
00:06:26,925 --> 00:06:28,565
- Let's give it a go.
- See how things go.

210
00:06:28,565 --> 00:06:29,635
We can do it.

211
00:06:29,635 --> 00:06:30,665
Let's do our best.

212
00:06:30,665 --> 00:06:31,695
(The goal is to arrive before 6pm!)

213
00:06:31,835 --> 00:06:33,205
We'll get going.

214
00:06:33,205 --> 00:06:34,405
Before you go,

215
00:06:34,565 --> 00:06:36,475
since it's a hot day,

216
00:06:36,475 --> 00:06:38,335
we'll give you each an ice cream.

217
00:06:38,335 --> 00:06:39,435
- What?
- Why?

218
00:06:39,775 --> 00:06:40,775
(Wow, ice cream.)

219
00:06:40,775 --> 00:06:41,775
- I think...
- We don't want it.

220
00:06:41,775 --> 00:06:42,775
- No, thanks.
- No, thanks.

221
00:06:42,775 --> 00:06:44,045
- There's more to it, right?
- There's more to it.

222
00:06:44,715 --> 00:06:46,745
They'd never give us something for no reason.

223
00:06:47,985 --> 00:06:49,215
That's really tasty.

224
00:06:49,215 --> 00:06:50,815
- That's tasty!
- That's really nice.

225
00:06:51,085 --> 00:06:52,485
- That ice cream...
- Give me that.

226
00:06:52,485 --> 00:06:53,555
It's really good.

227
00:06:53,555 --> 00:06:55,085
I'll be really annoyed if it's a game.

228
00:06:55,085 --> 00:06:56,285
This is...

229
00:06:56,695 --> 00:06:59,055
(For the members struggling in the heat)

230
00:06:59,665 --> 00:07:01,695
(A signature black sesame ice cream)

231
00:07:01,865 --> 00:07:03,765
They're giving it out. There's no secret trick.

232
00:07:04,095 --> 00:07:05,695
- They're different colors.
- Let's swap.

233
00:07:05,695 --> 00:07:06,705
Let's hear them out first.

234
00:07:06,705 --> 00:07:07,705
- Listen first.
- Let's swap.

235
00:07:07,705 --> 00:07:08,935
Don't taste it yet.

236
00:07:08,935 --> 00:07:10,635
Let me explain the rules.

237
00:07:10,935 --> 00:07:12,275
Keep them away from your faces.

238
00:07:12,435 --> 00:07:13,675
- The ice cream.
- Yes.

239
00:07:14,245 --> 00:07:15,875
- Do you see that car?
- Yes.

240
00:07:17,215 --> 00:07:18,845
You must finish your ice cream...

241
00:07:18,845 --> 00:07:21,015
to get in the car and head to where...

242
00:07:21,415 --> 00:07:23,555
the next mission will take place.

243
00:07:23,555 --> 00:07:24,885
- I didn't eat breakfast.
- It'll take no time.

244
00:07:24,885 --> 00:07:26,185
- It's quite a lot.
- Everyone.

245
00:07:26,185 --> 00:07:28,625
- It's a lot.
- The car leaves now.

246
00:07:28,825 --> 00:07:30,125
- What?
- No...

247
00:07:30,195 --> 00:07:31,825
- What?
- What are you saying?

248
00:07:31,825 --> 00:07:34,395
(The car is really leaving.)

249
00:07:34,965 --> 00:07:36,995
(Catch me if you can.)

250
00:07:37,635 --> 00:07:40,005
(The car leaves now.)

251
00:07:40,005 --> 00:07:41,335
- What?
- What are you saying?

252
00:07:41,335 --> 00:07:43,935
(Inhaling ice cream)

253
00:07:44,475 --> 00:07:46,805
(Unlike the veterans who start eating right away...)

254
00:07:47,145 --> 00:07:49,045
I start eating now?

255
00:07:49,405 --> 00:07:50,545
- Now?
- Everyone.

256
00:07:51,275 --> 00:07:52,315
(Glancing)

257
00:07:52,315 --> 00:07:55,385
(Hurriedly starting to eat once he understands the situation)

258
00:07:55,385 --> 00:07:56,555
(The members, the members' car)

259
00:07:56,555 --> 00:07:58,455
(The car is getting further away.)

260
00:07:58,455 --> 00:08:01,285
You can get in the car once you finish your ice cream.

261
00:08:01,385 --> 00:08:03,525
- I can't finish...
- Eat it up.

262
00:08:03,655 --> 00:08:04,955
It takes too long.

263
00:08:04,955 --> 00:08:06,055
My head aches.

264
00:08:06,055 --> 00:08:07,465
(Suffering from brain freeze)

265
00:08:07,725 --> 00:08:08,725
(My teeth ache.)

266
00:08:08,725 --> 00:08:09,965
I can't eat on the way, can I?

267
00:08:10,435 --> 00:08:12,135
It's good, but my teeth are sensitive.

268
00:08:12,595 --> 00:08:14,035
I must melt it as I go.

269
00:08:14,035 --> 00:08:15,135
- Yes.
- Right?

270
00:08:15,135 --> 00:08:16,705
Melt it as I eat.

271
00:08:16,735 --> 00:08:18,175
Turn it into a soup.

272
00:08:18,175 --> 00:08:19,205
Yes.

273
00:08:19,205 --> 00:08:20,205
Come on.

274
00:08:20,205 --> 00:08:21,745
(How far did it go?)

275
00:08:21,745 --> 00:08:23,005
(The members, the members' car)

276
00:08:23,005 --> 00:08:24,415
(It reached the hill in no time.)

277
00:08:24,415 --> 00:08:25,445
It's fast.

278
00:08:25,815 --> 00:08:28,585
- Hey, this is...
- My head hurts.

279
00:08:28,815 --> 00:08:31,015
(The car waits for no man.)

280
00:08:31,615 --> 00:08:33,455
- Oh, gosh.
- Would you like some?

281
00:08:37,555 --> 00:08:39,225
- I don't see the car.
- Where's the car?

282
00:08:39,325 --> 00:08:40,525
I don't see the car.

283
00:08:40,525 --> 00:08:42,065
Where's the car? Melt the ice cream.

284
00:08:42,195 --> 00:08:43,535
Melt it and drink it.

285
00:08:43,565 --> 00:08:45,635
(Just then)

286
00:08:46,035 --> 00:08:47,635
Whoever finished theirs...

287
00:08:47,635 --> 00:08:49,265
- can go first.
- Who's with me?

288
00:08:49,265 --> 00:08:50,775
- We must go together.
- No.

289
00:08:50,775 --> 00:08:52,805
We can go and stop the car.

290
00:08:53,605 --> 00:08:54,675
Yes. I'll stop the car.

291
00:08:54,675 --> 00:08:56,645
(It's pretty far even for the first finisher.)

292
00:08:57,215 --> 00:08:58,875
Can I stop the car if I catch up?

293
00:08:58,875 --> 00:09:00,215
(I should be able to catch up with the car, right?)

294
00:09:01,315 --> 00:09:02,415
The stairs.

295
00:09:03,015 --> 00:09:04,085
Gosh, I'm tired.

296
00:09:05,055 --> 00:09:06,085
Darn.

297
00:09:06,255 --> 00:09:07,255
(Grunting)

298
00:09:07,525 --> 00:09:08,685
(Somebody help Se Yoon.)

299
00:09:08,685 --> 00:09:09,725
Gosh, I'm already tired.

300
00:09:09,895 --> 00:09:13,765
(He climbs up the stairs without stopping for a moment.)

301
00:09:14,025 --> 00:09:16,295
I'm out of breath. I can't catch up.

302
00:09:17,365 --> 00:09:19,905
(But he's getting close to the car.)

303
00:09:21,265 --> 00:09:22,265
Yes.

304
00:09:23,475 --> 00:09:24,505
(At this rate, I won't be able to leave.)

305
00:09:24,505 --> 00:09:25,705
Could you eat some of mine?

306
00:09:26,475 --> 00:09:27,905
(I'll help you, Jong Min.)

307
00:09:27,905 --> 00:09:29,145
You have so much ice cream left.

308
00:09:29,145 --> 00:09:30,545
Gosh. What are we going to do?

309
00:09:30,545 --> 00:09:32,075
- I can't. My teeth hurt so much.
- Jong Min.

310
00:09:32,075 --> 00:09:33,415
No more, Jong Min.

311
00:09:33,645 --> 00:09:35,085
- Hey.
- I can't eat more. No more.

312
00:09:35,085 --> 00:09:36,615
You're on fire now.

313
00:09:36,615 --> 00:09:38,215
- No more, Jong Min.
- The middle-aged ladies love you.

314
00:09:38,215 --> 00:09:39,255
(I was almost done.)

315
00:09:39,315 --> 00:09:40,655
I was almost done with mine.

316
00:09:40,655 --> 00:09:43,525
(He's back to square one because of the oldest.)

317
00:09:44,525 --> 00:09:46,865
(Meanwhile, DinDin finishes his ice cream.)

318
00:09:47,025 --> 00:09:48,095
DinDin can leave now.

319
00:09:48,095 --> 00:09:50,065
(DinDin runs out to stop the car.)

320
00:09:50,995 --> 00:09:52,235
This is so annoying.

321
00:09:53,095 --> 00:09:54,765
I knew the ice cream was too good to be true.

322
00:09:54,765 --> 00:09:56,735
(They wouldn't give us ice cream just to be nice.)

323
00:09:56,735 --> 00:10:00,045
(DinDin, Se Yoon, their car)

324
00:10:01,405 --> 00:10:02,575
- Me.
- I love this ice cream.

325
00:10:02,575 --> 00:10:04,175
- Okay. Joon, go now.
- I finished.

326
00:10:04,175 --> 00:10:05,215
(Joon leaves next.)

327
00:10:05,215 --> 00:10:06,345
Where did they go?

328
00:10:06,345 --> 00:10:07,945
(Yong Jin finishes his ice cream too.)

329
00:10:07,945 --> 00:10:09,315
- Yong Jin, you can go.
- Let's go.

330
00:10:10,715 --> 00:10:14,185
(Diligent Taek finishes every bite of the ice cream...)

331
00:10:14,185 --> 00:10:16,255
(even if he's in a hurry.)

332
00:10:16,255 --> 00:10:18,255
- Ki Taek, you can go.
- Okay.

333
00:10:18,255 --> 00:10:19,395
(Ki Taek also finishes his ice cream.)

334
00:10:19,395 --> 00:10:20,395
I'm leaving.

335
00:10:20,625 --> 00:10:24,465
(The oldest member remains all alone.)

336
00:10:24,695 --> 00:10:27,005
I have a crazy brain freeze.

337
00:10:28,735 --> 00:10:29,735
Come back.

338
00:10:29,735 --> 00:10:30,975
(Meanwhile, Se Yoon is still running.)

339
00:10:31,135 --> 00:10:32,875
Gosh, I'm here.

340
00:10:33,805 --> 00:10:35,845
- All six of you must be here.
- What?

341
00:10:36,045 --> 00:10:37,245
All six of you must be here...

342
00:10:37,245 --> 00:10:39,145
- Stop this nonsense.
- This is dangerous, Se Yoon.

343
00:10:39,415 --> 00:10:40,485
Gosh, I should have walked.

344
00:10:40,485 --> 00:10:41,915
(He doesn't have the energy to get angry.)

345
00:10:41,915 --> 00:10:42,945
I'm so tired.

346
00:10:43,355 --> 00:10:44,685
I climbed up the stairs without taking a break.

347
00:10:44,685 --> 00:10:46,185
(Let me get in. I really ran as hard as I could.)

348
00:10:46,785 --> 00:10:48,455
(Director Ogre won't make it easy for him.)

349
00:10:49,085 --> 00:10:50,355
I want to use the restroom.

350
00:10:51,295 --> 00:10:52,395
Where's the car?

351
00:10:53,425 --> 00:10:55,665
My gosh. Jong Min has to come too.

352
00:10:56,395 --> 00:10:59,295
(He's still trying to finish the ice cream.)

353
00:10:59,765 --> 00:11:03,035
(Jong Min picks up the speed toward the end.)

354
00:11:03,275 --> 00:11:05,605
- Jong Min, you can go.
- Gosh. Let's go.

355
00:11:05,605 --> 00:11:07,375
Hurry. Try to catch up with them.

356
00:11:08,045 --> 00:11:10,775
My gosh. The lavenders here are indeed beautiful.

357
00:11:10,775 --> 00:11:12,375
(He doesn't have time to admire the view.)

358
00:11:13,445 --> 00:11:14,785
Hurry. All of us must be here.

359
00:11:15,545 --> 00:11:16,985
(DinDin arrives in no time.)

360
00:11:17,315 --> 00:11:19,055
Can't we just stand in front of the car?

361
00:11:19,055 --> 00:11:20,085
(Block the car.)

362
00:11:20,085 --> 00:11:22,285
- No. It's dangerous.
- What?

363
00:11:22,525 --> 00:11:25,025
No. It's dangerous.

364
00:11:25,125 --> 00:11:26,965
- Okay. Go slowly then.
- Okay. I'll go slowly.

365
00:11:26,965 --> 00:11:28,765
- Oh, no. It hurts!
- No!

366
00:11:28,925 --> 00:11:30,065
(The car has come to a stop.)

367
00:11:30,065 --> 00:11:31,835
(He even fakes an injury.)

368
00:11:31,995 --> 00:11:33,405
Why are you doing this to me?

369
00:11:33,565 --> 00:11:35,235
- They're here.
- Why are you doing this?

370
00:11:35,705 --> 00:11:36,835
- Where's Jong Min? Hurry!
- They're here.

371
00:11:36,835 --> 00:11:37,905
(Yong Jin, Joon, and Ki Taek arrive at the same time.)

372
00:11:38,035 --> 00:11:39,305
Block the car.

373
00:11:39,605 --> 00:11:40,975
- We can't.
- We can't?

374
00:11:40,975 --> 00:11:42,075
(Having the same thought)

375
00:11:42,605 --> 00:11:44,815
You need to step on the brake since it's going down.

376
00:11:44,915 --> 00:11:46,045
I'm doing that.

377
00:11:46,215 --> 00:11:48,345
- Jong Min is here. Get out.
- Darn.

378
00:11:49,385 --> 00:11:51,115
- Okay.
- My gosh.

379
00:11:51,115 --> 00:11:52,215
(This is exhausting. Get in.)

380
00:11:53,425 --> 00:11:55,325
- Gosh.
- Turn on the AC.

381
00:11:55,855 --> 00:11:58,825
Gosh, things are getting tough even from the get-go.

382
00:11:59,425 --> 00:12:01,895
- You know what?
- They might force us to get out.

383
00:12:02,165 --> 00:12:04,535
- What? Force us to get out?
- Yes, once it's past 6pm.

384
00:12:04,735 --> 00:12:07,005
Right. We'll be on the road like this.

385
00:12:07,405 --> 00:12:09,535
If we take Route Seven now,

386
00:12:09,665 --> 00:12:11,505
the GPS says we can be there in 4 hours and 20 minutes.

387
00:12:11,605 --> 00:12:12,635
- Gosh.
- Really?

388
00:12:12,635 --> 00:12:13,945
- If we just go straight there?
- Yes.

389
00:12:14,745 --> 00:12:16,475
- We'd arrive by 2pm without games.
- Right.

390
00:12:16,475 --> 00:12:17,875
(It's quite far even if they started from Donghae.)

391
00:12:18,045 --> 00:12:19,475
- This is...
- We might be able to do it.

392
00:12:19,475 --> 00:12:21,445
- We have four hours for missions.
- Right.

393
00:12:21,685 --> 00:12:23,885
We're headed to Samcheok. Right?

394
00:12:24,285 --> 00:12:25,655
- Samcheok.
- Probably.

395
00:12:25,655 --> 00:12:27,425
Yes. Samcheok. And we'll go south from there.

396
00:12:27,525 --> 00:12:30,295
Gosh. Imagine if Jong Min drew Goseong?

397
00:12:30,295 --> 00:12:31,395
It could've been really bad.

398
00:12:31,395 --> 00:12:33,365
Goseong is 200km away from here.

399
00:12:33,765 --> 00:12:35,995
(Their total distance could've been 480km if he drew Goseong.)

400
00:12:36,295 --> 00:12:38,165
I really tried my best for it.

401
00:12:38,295 --> 00:12:40,265
It didn't require any effort. You just spun the wheel.

402
00:12:41,205 --> 00:12:42,535
Well, he was born lucky.

403
00:12:43,205 --> 00:12:45,005
- He's one lucky guy.
- I'm grateful.

404
00:12:45,635 --> 00:12:47,805
Gosh, I'm getting a feeling today will be a long day.

405
00:12:47,805 --> 00:12:50,215
(Will they be able to arrive at the destination before 6pm?)

406
00:12:50,215 --> 00:12:51,445
This is where Ki Taek was stationed.

407
00:12:51,445 --> 00:12:53,245
- Right. I was.
- Where in Samcheok?

408
00:12:53,245 --> 00:12:55,245
- What's famous in Samcheok?
- Samcheok has...

409
00:12:55,245 --> 00:12:58,055
Jangho Port. Back then, it was nicknamed Naples of Korea.

410
00:12:58,055 --> 00:12:59,715
It was quite trendy...

411
00:12:59,715 --> 00:13:01,955
when I was stationed here.

412
00:13:02,725 --> 00:13:05,455
(Jangho Port, Naples of Korea)

413
00:13:05,455 --> 00:13:06,455
The Candlestick Rock.

414
00:13:06,455 --> 00:13:08,165
- I see. I know what it is.
- It's famous.

415
00:13:08,525 --> 00:13:12,365
(Miin Waterfall, the Grand Canyon of Korea)

416
00:13:12,365 --> 00:13:14,805
- Don't people come here to snorkel?
- It's a popular snorkeling spot.

417
00:13:14,805 --> 00:13:15,805
- There's the ocean.
- Right.

418
00:13:15,805 --> 00:13:18,375
- There are transparent kayaks.
- I know.

419
00:13:18,375 --> 00:13:20,375
Kayaking today could kill us. It's too hot.

420
00:13:20,375 --> 00:13:21,445
Right.

421
00:13:21,445 --> 00:13:24,175
I'm worried that we might end up getting wet.

422
00:13:24,615 --> 00:13:26,885
- I agree.
- We're by the ocean.

423
00:13:27,315 --> 00:13:29,215
Yong Jin, how many pairs of underwear did you pack?

424
00:13:29,215 --> 00:13:31,115
- This time, I packed extras.
- Did you pack a lot?

425
00:13:31,115 --> 00:13:32,315
- Yes.
- That's good.

426
00:13:32,315 --> 00:13:33,525
I brought two pairs which is a lot.

427
00:13:34,825 --> 00:13:36,025
- That's not a lot.
- That's not a lot.

428
00:13:36,025 --> 00:13:37,525
- Including the one I'm wearing.
- Gosh.

429
00:13:37,755 --> 00:13:39,225
- Gosh.
- Really?

430
00:13:39,495 --> 00:13:41,195
- Should we have brought three?
- Gosh.

431
00:13:41,195 --> 00:13:42,325
- Three?
- Three?

432
00:13:42,325 --> 00:13:43,495
- I packed 4.
- I packed 3.

433
00:13:43,495 --> 00:13:44,495
You packed three pairs?

434
00:13:44,495 --> 00:13:47,305
Well, I can borrow a pair from DinDin and Joon.

435
00:13:48,205 --> 00:13:50,605
(Silent)

436
00:13:50,635 --> 00:13:52,675
(I'm joking.)

437
00:13:53,745 --> 00:13:56,205
(As they continue driving, they enter Samcheok in no time.)

438
00:13:56,505 --> 00:13:58,115
- There's the ocean on our left.
- There's the ocean.

439
00:13:58,475 --> 00:14:01,415
Now, we're driving along the coast.

440
00:14:01,485 --> 00:14:02,685
Joon, are we going to the beach?

441
00:14:03,285 --> 00:14:04,715
- I think so.
- Are we here?

442
00:14:04,955 --> 00:14:07,185
All right. The HQ is calling us for the mission.

443
00:14:07,185 --> 00:14:08,355
Listen up. Go ahead.

444
00:14:08,355 --> 00:14:09,825
- Everyone.
- Yes.

445
00:14:09,825 --> 00:14:11,995
- Open the glove compartment.
- The glove compartment?

446
00:14:11,995 --> 00:14:13,155
- Okay.
- The glove compartment.

447
00:14:13,495 --> 00:14:16,525
Your next mission spot is marked on the map.

448
00:14:16,525 --> 00:14:17,665
- Really?
- What?

449
00:14:17,665 --> 00:14:18,795
- When did they put that in?
- It's right here.

450
00:14:18,795 --> 00:14:21,335
A parking lot, an outfit-changing spot, and a mission spot.

451
00:14:21,335 --> 00:14:22,335
- Then...
- An outfit-changing spot?

452
00:14:22,335 --> 00:14:23,335
- We have to change?
- We have to change?

453
00:14:23,335 --> 00:14:24,435
- We have to change?
- We have to change?

454
00:14:24,435 --> 00:14:26,805
We have to change. So we might end up in the water.

455
00:14:26,805 --> 00:14:28,575
Gosh, I don't want to end up in the water.

456
00:14:28,575 --> 00:14:30,875
We don't usually change outfits before going into the water.

457
00:14:31,175 --> 00:14:32,945
No. We might do a snorkeling activity.

458
00:14:33,515 --> 00:14:35,145
- No way.
- To do that,

459
00:14:35,145 --> 00:14:36,245
- That sounds so fun.
- we have to wear the suit.

460
00:14:36,245 --> 00:14:37,555
- Really?
- That sounds really fun.

461
00:14:37,555 --> 00:14:39,215
Samcheok is a famous destination for snorkeling.

462
00:14:39,615 --> 00:14:41,225
- For your information, - Yes.

463
00:14:41,655 --> 00:14:42,725
I'm a licensed scuba diver.

464
00:14:42,725 --> 00:14:43,725
- Skin diving?
- Yes.

465
00:14:43,725 --> 00:14:44,795
- Really?
- Yes.

466
00:14:44,795 --> 00:14:46,225
- You have so many licenses.
- I do.

467
00:14:46,625 --> 00:14:47,895
Do you want to hear something funny?

468
00:14:47,895 --> 00:14:49,495
I'm also a licensed auto mechanic.

469
00:14:49,565 --> 00:14:51,735
- Really?
- When did you get the license?

470
00:14:51,735 --> 00:14:53,395
I just studied for it when I had time.

471
00:14:53,395 --> 00:14:54,505
That's impressive.

472
00:14:55,365 --> 00:14:56,875
Hey, we're going snorkeling.

473
00:14:57,075 --> 00:14:59,135
When you change, check the back too, Ki Taek.

474
00:14:59,135 --> 00:15:00,175
Okay.

475
00:15:00,677 --> 00:15:01,499
I see transparent kayaks.

476
00:15:01,499 --> 00:15:03,409
- It's for two people.
- The water is so clean.

477
00:15:05,139 --> 00:15:07,139
Right here. We can change our outfits here.

478
00:15:07,609 --> 00:15:09,279
What should we change into?

479
00:15:10,709 --> 00:15:11,809
(What did Se Yoon spot?)

480
00:15:11,809 --> 00:15:13,219
It looks like all of us are going in.

481
00:15:14,019 --> 00:15:15,049
What is it?

482
00:15:15,049 --> 00:15:16,719
(Life vests and helmets)

483
00:15:16,719 --> 00:15:17,889
We have to wear helmets.

484
00:15:18,089 --> 00:15:20,119
- We'll end up in the water.
- Yes, we'll be in the water.

485
00:15:20,119 --> 00:15:21,519
- I guess we'll go into the water.
- Yes.

486
00:15:21,859 --> 00:15:24,459
What are we doing? Why do we need to change?

487
00:15:24,459 --> 00:15:26,699
(There's no time to get angry. We must hurry.)

488
00:15:28,029 --> 00:15:30,729
(As they're in a rush, they change outside.)

489
00:15:30,729 --> 00:15:33,269
Look at the time. We have to walk there.

490
00:15:35,739 --> 00:15:36,909
DinDin, change quickly.

491
00:15:37,169 --> 00:15:38,469
Why are there swim fins?

492
00:15:38,909 --> 00:15:41,009
I'm excited to do the missions as a group.

493
00:15:42,339 --> 00:15:43,749
It's nothing to get excited about.

494
00:15:44,179 --> 00:15:45,179
I'm so excited.

495
00:15:45,479 --> 00:15:47,749
You have these catchphrases in a funny tone.

496
00:15:48,179 --> 00:15:49,849
Did you get inspired in your day-to-day life?

497
00:15:50,149 --> 00:15:52,119
"Wait, this is going to be fun." Is that how you came to find it?

498
00:15:52,119 --> 00:15:53,559
I was trying out different things and got lucky.

499
00:15:53,559 --> 00:15:55,189
- You just got lucky?
- Yes.

500
00:15:55,619 --> 00:15:56,859
(They spent 6 minutes on changing.)

501
00:15:56,859 --> 00:15:58,489
Hey, hurry. We don't have much time.

502
00:15:59,129 --> 00:16:00,199
We don't have much time.

503
00:16:00,729 --> 00:16:02,659
Can't we do it after 45 minutes?

504
00:16:03,029 --> 00:16:04,699
Let's watch the second half. What do you think?

505
00:16:04,699 --> 00:16:06,299
(DinDin the Brat wants to cheer for the national team.)

506
00:16:06,839 --> 00:16:08,239
We need to cheer for our team.

507
00:16:08,239 --> 00:16:10,039
(They finish changing in 8 minutes and 30 seconds.)

508
00:16:10,239 --> 00:16:11,409
We look like the Red Devils.

509
00:16:11,409 --> 00:16:13,109
- We're the Red Devils.
- Right.

510
00:16:13,109 --> 00:16:14,109
Yes.

511
00:16:14,109 --> 00:16:15,879
