- That's right.

1023
00:32:38,959 --> 00:32:40,259
(He sets out again in resignation.)

1024
00:32:40,259 --> 00:32:41,759
- Go, Ki Taek.
- I'll be back.

1025
00:32:41,759 --> 00:32:43,399
- Hurry back.
- Quickly.

1026
00:32:43,399 --> 00:32:44,699
(Ki Taek's ninth round trip starts.)

1027
00:32:44,699 --> 00:32:45,699
Go.

1028
00:32:45,699 --> 00:32:47,499
I don't think Ki Taek knew the answer.

1029
00:32:47,739 --> 00:32:49,199
He doesn't seem disappointed.

1030
00:32:49,269 --> 00:32:52,839
That's not true. I knew the answer.

1031
00:32:52,939 --> 00:32:54,579
Maybe he thought that it was Edison.

1032
00:32:54,579 --> 00:32:57,279
- I don't think Ki Taek knew.
- He doesn't look disappointed.

1033
00:32:57,709 --> 00:33:00,449
That's not true. I knew the answer.

1034
00:33:00,579 --> 00:33:04,079
We need to verify Ki Taek's level of knowledge.

1035
00:33:04,319 --> 00:33:07,149
Hurry up. We don't have much time.

1036
00:33:07,389 --> 00:33:08,389
(Ki Taek with blurry eyes)

1037
00:33:08,389 --> 00:33:10,259
(Eyes going blank from long hours of swimming)

1038
00:33:10,359 --> 00:33:12,659
What's important is coming back and answering correctly.

1039
00:33:13,129 --> 00:33:14,959
(I'll definitely get it this time.)

1040
00:33:14,959 --> 00:33:16,299
(Pushing through)

1041
00:33:16,299 --> 00:33:17,399
When did he come back?

1042
00:33:17,399 --> 00:33:18,599
- He's back. Hurry up.
- He's back.

1043
00:33:18,699 --> 00:33:19,769
Let's go.

1044
00:33:19,769 --> 00:33:21,399
- Okay, he's back. Hurry up.
- He's back.

1045
00:33:21,399 --> 00:33:22,539
All right, everyone.

1046
00:33:22,539 --> 00:33:24,069
- Don't tell him the answer.
- Okay.

1047
00:33:24,069 --> 00:33:26,309
Mister, give the question more quickly. We have no time.

1048
00:33:26,639 --> 00:33:28,309
What's the name of the master who painted...

1049
00:33:28,409 --> 00:33:29,809
- The Last Supper...
- You know this, right?

1050
00:33:29,879 --> 00:33:31,479
and the Mona Lisa?

1051
00:33:31,479 --> 00:33:33,209
(What's the name of the master?)

1052
00:33:33,209 --> 00:33:34,749
It's not Cho Yong Pil. What's his name?

1053
00:33:35,079 --> 00:33:36,619
One, two...

1054
00:33:36,619 --> 00:33:37,649
(Will Ki Taek know the answer?)

1055
00:33:37,649 --> 00:33:38,649
Three.

1056
00:33:38,649 --> 00:33:40,049
(Get it right, Ki Taek.)

1057
00:33:40,619 --> 00:33:41,819
Leonardo da Vinci.

1058
00:33:41,819 --> 00:33:43,059
- Oh, he knows.
- That's right.

1059
00:33:43,319 --> 00:33:45,259
As you know, The Last Supper is by Leonardo da Vinci.

1060
00:33:45,259 --> 00:33:46,559
Ki Taek is correct.

1061
00:33:46,559 --> 00:33:47,899
- Yes.
- That's right.

1062
00:33:47,899 --> 00:33:50,729
Actually, I got confused with Gauss.

1063
00:33:50,829 --> 00:33:51,869
Gauss?

1064
00:33:51,999 --> 00:33:53,329
- Gauss?
- Don't you mean Gaudi?

1065
00:33:53,329 --> 00:33:54,439
Isn't it Gaudi?

1066
00:33:54,439 --> 00:33:55,639
Is it Gaudi?

1067
00:33:55,969 --> 00:33:57,299
Gaudi was an architect.

1068
00:33:57,769 --> 00:33:59,339
Tell us honestly. Didn't you think...

1069
00:33:59,339 --> 00:34:01,309
- that Einstein was Edison?
- No way.

1070
00:34:01,309 --> 00:34:03,109
- I knew that it was Einstein.
- Yong Jin got it right, but...

1071
00:34:03,309 --> 00:34:05,479
(We plan to verify his knowledge soon.)

1072
00:34:05,649 --> 00:34:07,549
Everyone, once you come out of the water,

1073
00:34:07,549 --> 00:34:09,779
I'll tell you about the next mission location.

1074
00:34:09,779 --> 00:34:10,989
Get yourselves together.

1075
00:34:10,989 --> 00:34:12,489
Move out once you're ready.

1076
00:34:12,489 --> 00:34:14,019
Okay, we're coming.

1077
00:34:14,019 --> 00:34:15,089
(Current time)

1078
00:34:15,089 --> 00:34:16,959
Okay, let's go. Run.

1079
00:34:16,959 --> 00:34:18,229
(2 Days 1 Night)

1080
00:34:18,389 --> 00:34:21,229
If we don't hurry, we'll have to walk.

1081
00:34:21,229 --> 00:34:22,429
(If we're late, we'll be on foot.)

1082
00:34:24,059 --> 00:34:27,699
(They rush to the regrouping point.)

1083
00:34:28,539 --> 00:34:33,909
(Straight to the shower upon arrival)

1084
00:34:34,979 --> 00:34:41,949
(Everyone gets ready swiftly.)

1085
00:34:43,079 --> 00:34:46,149
(Slathering on sunscreen in a hurry)

1086
00:34:49,089 --> 00:34:50,819
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

1087
00:34:51,029 --> 00:34:52,229
- Let's go.
- We don't have time.

1088
00:34:52,259 --> 00:34:53,629
We're very short on time.

1089
00:34:53,629 --> 00:34:54,859
(They get ready fast and head to the next location.)

1090
00:34:54,859 --> 00:34:56,029
Right now...

1091
00:34:56,659 --> 00:34:57,869
- We spent...
- We wasted...

1092
00:34:57,869 --> 00:34:59,899
- too much time here.
- Goodness.

1093
00:35:00,429 --> 00:35:02,039
- Isn't this a race?
- Yes.

1094
00:35:02,269 --> 00:35:03,599
By the way,

1095
00:35:03,599 --> 00:35:05,039
would you like some smoothies?

1096
00:35:05,709 --> 00:35:07,109
(All of a sudden)

1097
00:35:07,109 --> 00:35:08,539
(A smoothie?)

1098
00:35:08,879 --> 00:35:10,909
Yes, I'd love some.

1099
00:35:10,909 --> 00:35:12,749
- Even if you're in a hurry?
- It's okay. I still want some.

1100
00:35:12,749 --> 00:35:13,809
We want some.

1101
00:35:13,909 --> 00:35:15,379
(A smoothie all of a sudden?)

1102
00:35:15,379 --> 00:35:16,379
But we're in a hurry.

1103
00:35:16,379 --> 00:35:17,649
(There's something fishy about it.)

1104
00:35:17,649 --> 00:35:18,689
- Do we have time to eat?
- I want some.

1105
00:35:18,689 --> 00:35:21,819
I bet he's trying to make us waste time.

1106
00:35:21,819 --> 00:35:23,189
(There's no way he's being nice to us.)

1107
00:35:23,189 --> 00:35:24,289
- No, listen.
- He's trying to trick us.

1108
00:35:24,289 --> 00:35:25,859
Making a smoothie won't take long.

1109
00:35:26,059 --> 00:35:27,459
What's that? Is it money?

1110
00:35:27,459 --> 00:35:29,029
- Yes, I gave you a lot of money.
- Do we buy it?

1111
00:35:29,029 --> 00:35:30,859
Can we have some fishcakes?

1112
00:35:30,859 --> 00:35:32,099
- What about a corn dog?
- I'm so hungry...

1113
00:35:32,099 --> 00:35:33,369
- from playing in the water.
- It's 20 dollars.

1114
00:35:33,499 --> 00:35:34,639
- What?
- Can I have a corn dog?

1115
00:35:34,639 --> 00:35:35,669
Let's buy some coffee here.

1116
00:35:35,669 --> 00:35:36,869
- Let's get a corn dog.
- Can we really eat?

1117
00:35:36,869 --> 00:35:38,139
- Yes.
- Can I have a fishcake?

1118
00:35:38,439 --> 00:35:39,909
Let's hurry up.

1119
00:35:40,539 --> 00:35:41,539
Seriously?

1120
00:35:41,839 --> 00:35:43,839
- I want some broth.
- I'm hungry.

1121
00:35:44,079 --> 00:35:45,749
- Aren't you hungry?
- I am.

1122
00:35:46,749 --> 00:35:47,949
The fishcake looks good too.

1123
00:35:48,719 --> 00:35:51,119
- Jong Min, you want some fishcakes?
- Yes.

1124
00:35:51,389 --> 00:35:52,949
- Okay, you want one too?
- Yes.

1125
00:35:52,949 --> 00:35:54,189
That would be five dollars.

1126
00:35:54,189 --> 00:35:55,559
- What about you, Joon?
- I'll get a fishcake.

1127
00:35:55,559 --> 00:35:57,319
(Jong Min, Yong Jin, and Joon decide on the fishcake.)

1128
00:35:57,319 --> 00:35:58,859
Let's get a corn dog.

1129
00:35:58,859 --> 00:35:59,989
- Then...
- An old-fashioned corn dog.

1130
00:35:59,989 --> 00:36:01,659
Then all of us will get a corn dog.

1131
00:36:01,659 --> 00:36:04,029
- Old-fashioned corn dogs?
- I also want the old-fashioned.

1132
00:36:04,029 --> 00:36:05,999
(Se Yoon, Ki Taek, and DinDin choose corn dogs.)

1133
00:36:05,999 --> 00:36:07,329
I have to deep-fry them.

1134
00:36:07,329 --> 00:36:09,669
- You have to deep-fry them?
- Yes, these are just samples.

1135
00:36:09,669 --> 00:36:10,769
These are samples?

1136
00:36:11,039 --> 00:36:12,309
How long does it take to deep-fry them?

1137
00:36:12,309 --> 00:36:13,569
(Deep-frying takes 5 minutes.)

1138
00:36:14,009 --> 00:36:15,339
Just get fishcake.

1139
00:36:15,339 --> 00:36:18,209
(Eat fishcake that doesn't take long.)

1140
00:36:18,649 --> 00:36:20,079
Eat it without frying it.

1141
00:36:20,079 --> 00:36:21,379
Eat the uncooked batter.

1142
00:36:22,879 --> 00:36:24,149
These are samples?

1143
00:36:24,149 --> 00:36:25,449
- Then how long...
- How long does it take?

1144
00:36:25,449 --> 00:36:26,689
(Flustered Ki Taek)

1145
00:36:27,119 --> 00:36:28,619
We don't have time.

1146
00:36:28,619 --> 00:36:30,719
(We don't have time.)

1147
00:36:30,719 --> 00:36:31,759
Deep-frying will take...

1148
00:36:32,459 --> 00:36:34,629
Deep-frying will take a long time. We have to go soon.

1149
00:36:34,629 --> 00:36:36,399
I'll show you how I eat faster than you.

1150
00:36:36,729 --> 00:36:38,129
- Do you want this?
- Of course.

1151
00:36:38,129 --> 00:36:39,429
(In that case...)

1152
00:36:40,199 --> 00:36:41,339
It tastes so good.

1153
00:36:43,099 --> 00:36:44,439
Eating after playing in the water...

1154
00:36:44,439 --> 00:36:45,609
(Playing in the water isn't complete without snacks.)

1155
00:36:45,609 --> 00:36:47,209
It tastes so good after playing in the water.

1156
00:36:47,209 --> 00:36:48,909
(I agree.)

1157
00:36:49,209 --> 00:36:50,609
How much is iced Americano?

1158
00:36:50,609 --> 00:36:52,649
(How much is iced Americano?)

1159
00:36:52,649 --> 00:36:54,879
Are you just curious all of a sudden?

1160
00:36:55,019 --> 00:36:56,549
I definitely need some.

1161
00:36:57,949 --> 00:36:59,419
- That's it.
- Here you go.

1162
00:37:00,349 --> 00:37:01,719
What are you doing?

1163
00:37:03,259 --> 00:37:05,289
She gave us an iced Americano for free.

1164
00:37:05,289 --> 00:37:06,329
Thank you.

1165
00:37:06,589 --> 00:37:07,589
(Collecting immediately)

1166
00:37:07,589 --> 00:37:09,059
- That is...
- What?

1167
00:37:10,599 --> 00:37:11,869
Why did she give it for free?

1168
00:37:12,569 --> 00:37:14,969
Why are you taking it when she gave it to us?

1169
00:37:15,469 --> 00:37:17,399
You got a bad case of acting like a celebrity.

1170
00:37:17,399 --> 00:37:18,509
No, I don't.

1171
00:37:19,509 --> 00:37:20,509
Hey.

1172
00:37:20,509 --> 00:37:22,409
(The coffee disappeared right in front of him.)

1173
00:37:22,409 --> 00:37:24,379
- What?
- Ma'am, is it okay...

1174
00:37:24,909 --> 00:37:26,479
He's Joo Jong Hyun from KBS.

1175
00:37:26,479 --> 00:37:27,479
Okay.

1176
00:37:27,479 --> 00:37:28,819
Hurry up and eat.

1177
00:37:28,819 --> 00:37:29,819
- That's for you.
- I can eat fast.

1178
00:37:29,819 --> 00:37:31,149
Let me take care of this first.

1179
00:37:31,419 --> 00:37:32,849
The next one came out.

1180
00:37:33,149 --> 00:37:35,489
- It's deep-fried very nicely.
- We're late. We must go.

1181
00:37:35,489 --> 00:37:37,829
(Although he's in a hurry, he puts what's necessary.)

1182
00:37:37,829 --> 00:37:39,559
- Okay, let's go.
- Let's go.

1183
00:37:39,559 --> 00:37:41,329
(Although he's in a hurry, he puts what's necessary.)

1184
00:37:41,329 --> 00:37:42,929
It looks delicious.

1185
00:37:42,929 --> 00:37:43,929
(Setting off again for the destination)

1186
00:37:43,929 --> 00:37:45,099
- Thank you, ma'am.
- Thank you.

1187
00:37:45,099 --> 00:37:47,229
- Goodbye.
- Thank you.

1188
00:37:47,299 --> 00:37:48,339
Goodbye.

1189
00:37:49,399 --> 00:37:50,839
Thank you for the food.

1190
00:37:50,839 --> 00:37:52,339
(Sitting down to eat is a luxury.)

1191
00:37:52,339 --> 00:37:54,069
(Taking a bite on their way)

1192
00:37:54,239 --> 00:37:55,809
- Hurry up and get in.
- Eat.

1193
00:37:55,809 --> 00:37:57,039
We're getting in.

1194
00:37:57,039 --> 00:37:58,545
(They spent extra 9 minutes to eat snacks.)

1195
00:37:58,631 --> 00:37:59,901
- Give me the address now.
- Okay.

1196
00:38:00,826 --> 00:38:02,566
We're heading to the next mission.

1197
00:38:02,626 --> 00:38:03,696
- Okay.
- Okay.

1198
00:38:03,896 --> 00:38:05,096
The next mission location is...

1199
00:38:05,096 --> 00:38:06,296
Just open it.

1200
00:38:06,296 --> 00:38:07,506
- It is...
- It is...

1201
00:38:07,506 --> 00:38:08,506
Stop messing around.

1202
00:38:08,506 --> 00:38:10,006
It is this.

1203
00:38:11,136 --> 00:38:13,806
- Uljin.
- Jukbyeon-myeon, Uljin.

1204
00:38:14,099 --> 00:38:15,199
- Thirty?
- Thirty kilometers?

1205
00:38:15,199 --> 00:38:16,199
That's close.

1206
00:38:16,199 --> 00:38:17,869
- I'll start driving.
- Let's go.

1207
00:38:17,869 --> 00:38:19,099
(Setting off to Uljin at 12:02pm)

1208
00:38:19,339 --> 00:38:21,239
Did we spend two hours here?

1209
00:38:21,909 --> 00:38:23,039
We spent a long time here.

1210
00:38:23,039 --> 00:38:24,209
(Spent 2 hours in Samcheok)

1211
00:38:24,479 --> 00:38:27,009
By the way, why did we just eat fishcake?

1212
00:38:27,649 --> 00:38:28,779
We wanted to eat because it's delicious.

1213
00:38:28,779 --> 00:38:29,879
(Simple and clear)

1214
00:38:29,879 --> 00:38:32,249
He withdrew cash using the card,

1215
00:38:32,249 --> 00:38:33,419
so it's strange.

1216
00:38:33,719 --> 00:38:36,189
They're trying to eat up the time we have left.

1217
00:38:36,219 --> 00:38:37,989
Jong Min, there is...

1218
00:38:37,989 --> 00:38:39,659
Yeongdeok after Uljin.

1219
00:38:39,659 --> 00:38:40,659
Yeongdeok?

1220
00:38:40,659 --> 00:38:42,489
- There are Pohang and Gyeongju.
- Isn't there Pohang?

1221
00:38:42,489 --> 00:38:43,699
Really?

1222
00:38:43,699 --> 00:38:45,299
This won't be easy.

1223
00:38:45,299 --> 00:38:47,529
Really? If we aren't careful,

1224
00:38:47,929 --> 00:38:49,169
we might have to walk from Pohang.

1225
00:38:49,499 --> 00:38:52,969
From Pohang Station to Gyeongju Station,

1226
00:38:53,499 --> 00:38:55,039
it takes 40 minutes by car.

1227
00:38:55,869 --> 00:38:58,609
It takes more than nine hours by foot.

1228
00:38:58,609 --> 00:38:59,979
- That's impossible.
- No way.

1229
00:39:00,079 --> 00:39:02,609
- It takes 9 hours?
- We must walk more than 9 hours.

1230
00:39:02,609 --> 00:39:05,049
We would arrive early tomorrow morning.

1231
00:39:05,179 --> 00:39:06,719
They actually make you walk on the show.

1232
00:39:06,779 --> 00:39:07,989
- Of course.
- We'll be in trouble.

1233
00:39:07,989 --> 00:39:09,749
Right. They actually make you do it.

1234
00:39:09,749 --> 00:39:10,759
This is impossible.

1235
00:39:10,759 --> 00:39:11,859
(If they fail the race, they'll walk from there.)

1236
00:39:11,859 --> 00:39:14,429
We must get to Gyeongju as much as possible.

1237
00:39:14,959 --> 00:39:17,059
- Let's try to get there fast.
- Right.

1238
00:39:17,229 --> 00:39:20,569
We're traveling the whole backbone of South Korea.

1239
00:39:20,569 --> 00:39:21,599
We're moving along the backbone.

1240
00:39:21,599 --> 00:39:24,169
When you're driving alone, it's hard to enjoy the ocean view.

1241
00:39:24,169 --> 00:39:26,039
Thanks to Se Yoon driving, I can see the ocean.

1242
00:39:26,039 --> 00:39:27,809
Exactly. Take a look at the sea.

1243
00:39:27,809 --> 00:39:29,139
It's the East Sea on the left.

1244
00:39:29,209 --> 00:39:30,839
- Where?
- On the left.

1245
00:39:31,639 --> 00:39:34,509
Route Seven, the coastal highway.

1246
00:39:34,509 --> 00:39:36,279
(Route 7, embracing the East Sea)

1247
00:39:36,279 --> 00:39:38,749
I'd love to drive on Route Seven...

1248
00:39:38,749 --> 00:39:40,389
- That's the best.
- on a motorcycle.

1249
00:39:40,389 --> 00:39:41,389
(The race continues with the sea breeze.)

1250
00:39:42,089 --> 00:39:44,019
(As you follow the coastline with the blue East Sea by your side)

1251
00:39:44,659 --> 00:39:47,889
(Arriving in Uljin, North Gyeongsang Province)

1252
00:39:48,389 --> 00:39:50,429
(Seongnyu Cave, a natural cave shaped by nature)

1253
00:39:50,859 --> 00:39:52,199
(Jukbyeon Coast Skyrail)

1254
00:39:52,499 --> 00:39:53,899
(Deunggisan Skywalk)

1255
00:39:54,299 --> 00:39:55,829
(Wangpicheon Cable Car)

1256
00:39:56,599 --> 00:39:58,439
(Uljin, where pristine nature is alive)

1257
00:39:58,599 --> 00:40:01,039
I savored that corn dog,

1258
00:40:01,039 --> 00:40:02,139
and I'm even hungrier now.

1259
00:40:02,209 --> 00:40:03,809
- Aren't you suddenly hungry again?
- Yes.

1260
00:40:03,879 --> 00:40:05,439
It's time for lunch.

1261
00:40:05,709 --> 00:40:07,009
- I need some Korean food.
- You're right.

1262
00:40:07,379 --> 00:40:08,879
What's famous in Uljin?

1263
00:40:09,409 --> 00:40:11,749
- There's snow crab.
- Snow crab and squid.

1264
00:40:12,479 --> 00:40:13,649
- Are we there yet?
- We have one minute left.

1265
00:40:13,649 --> 00:40:14,819
One minute? We're almost there.

1266
00:40:16,089 --> 00:40:17,489
Isn't this it? It's this place.

1267
00:40:19,059 --> 00:40:20,459
- It's a restaurant.
- It's a restaurant.

1268
00:40:20,629 --> 00:40:23,059
- Okay.
- There's braised codfish head.

1269
00:40:23,059 --> 00:40:24,329
I like braised codfish head.

1270
00:40:24,359 --> 00:40:25,359
It's octopus soup!

1271
00:40:25,359 --> 00:40:26,999
