1433
00:45:49,349 --> 00:45:52,219
(We never said that it was 6 servings.)

1434
00:45:52,659 --> 00:45:54,259
Is this all?

1435
00:45:54,629 --> 00:45:55,729
Yes.

1436
00:45:56,589 --> 00:45:57,729
This is...

1437
00:45:57,899 --> 00:45:59,599
Let's eat it now and go.

1438
00:45:59,759 --> 00:46:01,369
- Let's spin it right away.
- Hold on.

1439
00:46:01,669 --> 00:46:04,439
(We got tricked again.)

1440
00:46:04,439 --> 00:46:05,839
I'll serve you now.

1441
00:46:05,839 --> 00:46:07,039
(The amount is small and cute for 6 men.)

1442
00:46:07,039 --> 00:46:08,209
In ten minutes...

1443
00:46:08,209 --> 00:46:10,369
Did we wait ten minutes for this little thing?

1444
00:46:10,369 --> 00:46:11,779
We waited ten minutes for this.

1445
00:46:11,779 --> 00:46:14,009
- That was harsh.
- My goodness.

1446
00:46:14,009 --> 00:46:16,049
The problem is that there's only one bowl of rice.

1447
00:46:16,049 --> 00:46:17,419
Take a bite and rotate.

1448
00:46:17,419 --> 00:46:19,119
Serve rice to everyone.

1449
00:46:19,119 --> 00:46:20,849
- How do I divide it into six?
- Divide it.

1450
00:46:21,219 --> 00:46:23,749
Food takes a long time to make, but we can eat it fast.

1451
00:46:23,749 --> 00:46:26,159
- Goodness.
- Can I divide it into six?

1452
00:46:26,159 --> 00:46:28,189
I won't eat any rice, so you guys eat it.

1453
00:46:28,189 --> 00:46:30,089
This is too little.

1454
00:46:30,729 --> 00:46:32,359
In a way, what Ki Taek drew...

1455
00:46:32,359 --> 00:46:34,629
