- Pohang?
- Yes.

2747
01:31:50,473 --> 01:31:52,773
- Are you a good driver?
- I'm not bad.

2748
01:31:52,773 --> 01:31:54,813
We've finally found out what Ki Taek is good at.

2749
01:31:54,813 --> 01:31:57,113
Ki Taek, it's okay to admit it if you're not good at it.

2750
01:31:57,113 --> 01:31:59,453
Our lives are on the line when you're driving.

2751
01:31:59,453 --> 01:32:00,853
I'm good at this.

2752
01:32:00,853 --> 01:32:02,253
The lives of six people depend on you.

2753
01:32:02,253 --> 01:32:05,723
I even perform my car stunt scenes myself.

2754
01:32:05,793 --> 01:32:07,293
- I can say I'm good at driving.
- All right.

2755
01:32:08,153 --> 01:32:09,763
Ki Taek, you're good at this.

2756
01:32:10,323 --> 01:32:11,563
He's only going straight.

2757
01:32:11,563 --> 01:32:12,793
(Despite all the worries, Ki Taek's driving is quite smooth.)

2758
01:32:12,793 --> 01:32:13,933
Thank you.

2759
01:32:14,533 --> 01:32:15,763
How did the mission end?

2760
01:32:15,933 --> 01:32:17,333
I was the last one to finish it.

2761
01:32:17,803 --> 01:32:20,203
Yong Jin, you weren't so good at it.

2762
01:32:20,203 --> 01:32:21,203
- You mean, the mission?
- Yes.

2763
01:32:21,203 --> 01:32:22,573
I just let the others finish first.

2764
01:32:23,503 --> 01:32:25,273
This is what he does.

2765
01:32:25,473 --> 01:32:26,773
He always says things like that.

2766
01:32:26,873 --> 01:32:28,683
- Do you want to go 1-on-1 with me?
- Yes.

2767
01:32:29,183 --> 01:32:30,643
You should watch it on TV later.

2768
01:32:31,413 --> 01:32:33,913
- Yong Jin is just confident.
- His confidence is high.

2769
01:32:33,913 --> 01:32:35,253
His confidence is sky-high.

2770
01:32:35,783 --> 01:32:39,253
(Will Yong Jin be able to redeem himself?)

2771
01:32:39,323 --> 01:32:41,123
(Next episode)

2772
01:32:41,623 --> 01:32:43,923
(A true variety show...)

2773
01:32:44,493 --> 01:32:46,933
(always begins when the rain starts to fall.)

2774
01:32:47,163 --> 01:32:52,003
(Six men who live as if there was no tomorrow)

2775
01:32:52,233 --> 01:32:55,543
(They are about to show...)

2776
01:32:55,843 --> 01:32:59,743
(the splash-filled showdown.)

2777
01:33:00,313 --> 01:33:02,613
(Chasing and being chased)

2778
01:33:02,613 --> 01:33:05,883
(The world where the law of the jungle prevails)

2779
01:33:06,313 --> 01:33:10,723
(Who will have the last laugh?)

2780
01:33:11,123 --> 01:33:14,223
(A midsummer night's camp is coming soon.)

2781
01:33:14,723 --> 01:33:15,893
Yes. Come on!

2782
01:33:15,893 --> 01:33:19,045
(See you next week.)
